---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";

/**
 * SSR (output:server): getStaticPaths is ignored, so Astro.props is empty at runtime.
 * Resolve the article from the URL slug instead of props (avoids crash on click).
 */
const posts = [
    {
      slug: "erreurs-taches-tapis",
      title: "3 Critical Mistakes to Avoid with Carpet Stains",
      excerpt:
        "Scrubbing is often the worst reaction. Learn what to do first to protect carpet fibers and improve stain removal results.",
      date: "December 17, 2024",
      category: "Maintenance",
      image: "🛑",
      content: `
        <p>Wine spills, coffee marks, and pet accidents happen quickly. The first reaction determines whether the stain can be removed safely.</p>
        <h3>Mistake #1: Scrubbing aggressively</h3>
        <p>Scrubbing spreads pigments and can damage carpet fibers. Always blot with a clean white towel instead of rubbing.</p>
        <h3>Mistake #2: Using random household products</h3>
        <p>Many DIY products leave sticky residue and can lock stains deeper. Use neutral products or ask a specialist for the right treatment.</p>
        <h3>Mistake #3: Waiting too long</h3>
        <p>Fresh stains are easier to remove than dried stains. Fast intervention significantly improves final results.</p>
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: "nettoyage-vapeur-vs-location",
      title: "Rental Machine vs Professional Truck-Mount",
      excerpt:
        "Rental tools can help with minor spots, but deep extraction and faster drying require professional equipment.",
      date: "December 15, 2024",
      category: "Comparatif",
      image: "🚛",
      content: `
        <p>Rental machines are convenient for superficial cleaning. For hygiene, extraction depth, and drying speed, truck-mount systems perform better.</p>
        <h3>1) Stronger extraction</h3>
        <p>Professional vacuum power removes much more moisture, reducing mold risk and downtime.</p>
        <h3>2) Stable hot water performance</h3>
        <p>Consistent heat improves soil breakdown and allergen removal.</p>
        <h3>3) Better chemistry control</h3>
        <p>Professional products and neutralization reduce sticky residues that cause rapid resoiling.</p>
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: "frequence-nettoyage-tapis",
      title: "How Often Should Carpets Be Professionally Cleaned?",
      excerpt:
        "Visible dirt appears late. Follow practical cleaning intervals based on home traffic, pets, and allergy sensitivity.",
      date: "December 10, 2024",
      category: "Health",
      image: "📅",
      content: `
        <p>Carpets trap dust, pollen, and allergens. Waiting until visible staining appears is usually too late for preventive maintenance.</p>
        <h3>Recommended intervals</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Standard household:</strong> every 12 to 18 months.</li>
          <li><strong>Families with children:</strong> every 6 to 12 months.</li>
          <li><strong>Homes with pets:</strong> about every 6 months.</li>
          <li><strong>Allergy-prone homes:</strong> every 4 to 6 months.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Health and durability benefits</h3>
        <p>Regular deep cleaning supports indoor air quality and extends carpet lifespan while preserving texture and appearance.</p>
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: "urine-animaux-tapis",
      title: "Pet Urine Odor: Why It Keeps Coming Back",
      excerpt:
        "Odors often return in humid weather because urine crystals remain deep in fibers and underlay.",
      date: "December 14, 2024",
      category: "Pets",
      image: "🐶",
      content: `
        <p>You may clean the surface and still notice odor later. This is usually caused by uric acid crystals left deep in carpet layers.</p>
        <h3>The chemistry behind recurring odor</h3>
        <p>When humidity rises, residual crystals reactivate and release ammonia-like odor again.</p>
        <h3>Why sprays are not enough</h3>
        <p>Most deodorizing sprays mask smell but do not remove the source.</p>
        <h3>What works</h3>
        <p>Targeted enzyme treatment combined with deep extraction is the most reliable approach for odor control.</p>
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: "preparer-visite-nettoyage",
      title: "A 5-Minute Checklist Before Your Cleaning Visit",
      excerpt:
        "Simple preparation steps to help your appointment run smoothly and efficiently.",
      date: "December 12, 2024",
      category: "Guide",
      image: "📋",
      content: `
        <p>A little preparation helps your technician work faster and deliver the best result.</p>
        <h3>1) Clear work areas</h3>
        <p>Move fragile items, toys, and small objects from the areas to be cleaned.</p>
        <h3>2) Furniture expectations</h3>
        <p>Most standard furniture can be moved, but heavy or sensitive items should stay in place for safety.</p>
        <h3>3) Light vacuuming (optional)</h3>
        <p>A quick vacuum pass can help remove surface debris before deep extraction.</p>
        <h3>4) Parking access</h3>
        <p>Closer truck access supports stronger heat and consistent equipment performance.</p>
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: "entretien-cuir-erreurs",
      title: "Leather Care Mistakes to Avoid",
      excerpt:
        "Everyday products can damage leather finish. Use a safer cleaning and conditioning routine.",
      date: "December 08, 2024",
      category: "Maintenance",
      image: "🛋️",
      content: `
        <p>Leather needs proper cleaning and conditioning. Incorrect products can accelerate wear and damage surface finish.</p>
        <h3>Avoid baby wipes and harsh household products</h3>
        <p>Many products contain chemicals that are not designed for leather and can weaken protective coating over time.</p>
        <h3>Avoid oily DIY treatments</h3>
        <p>Heavy oils can leave residue, attract dirt, and alter leather appearance.</p>
        <h3>A safer maintenance process</h3>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Dust weekly:</strong> Use a soft dry cloth.</li>
            <li><strong>Clean gently:</strong> Use a damp cloth for minor marks.</li>
            <li><strong>Condition periodically:</strong> Apply professional leather conditioner after proper cleaning.</li>
        </ol>
      `,
    },
  ];

const slug = Astro.params.slug;
const post = posts.find((p) => p.slug === slug);
if (!post) {
  return new Response(null, { status: 404, statusText: "Not Found" });
}
---

<Layout
  title={`${post.title} | Expert Tips | Empire Cleaning Group`}
  description={post.excerpt}
>
  <div class="article-header">
    <div class="container text-center fade-in-section">
      <span class="category-tag">{post.category}</span>
      <h1 class="text-gradient">{post.title}</h1>
      <p class="meta-date">Published on {post.date}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="article-layout">
        <!-- ARTICLE CONTENT -->
        <article class="article-content fade-in-section delay-100">
          <div class="content-body" set:html={post.content} />

          <div class="share-box">
            <p>Found this tip useful?</p>
            <a href="/en/conseils" class="back-link">&larr; Back to expert tips</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- SIDEBAR -->
        <aside class="article-sidebar">
          <div class="sticky-card fade-in-section">
            <h3 class="card-title text-gradient-gold">Need a Pro?</h3>
            <p class="card-desc">
              Protect your carpets and upholstery with professional care.
            </p>

            <a
              href="tel:5148939939"
              class="btn btn-primary full-width pulse-phone"
            >
              <span class="icon">📞</span> (514) 893-9939
            </a>

            <div class="service-links" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
              <strong>Our services:</strong>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <a href="/en/services/nettoyage-tapis-residentiel"
                    >Residential Carpet Cleaning</a
                  >
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/en/services/meubles-tissu">Upholstery Cleaning</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="/en/services/nettoyage-desinfection-matelas"
                    >Mattress Cleaning</a
                  >
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-header {
    background: var(--color-bg-light-blue);
    padding: 6rem 0 4rem 0;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .category-tag {
    background: white;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    padding: 5px 15px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .meta-date {
    color: #888;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .article-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  /* Content Styling */
  .article-content {
    background: white;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .content-body {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #444;
  }

  /* Global styles for injected HTML content */
  :global(.content-body h3) {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  :global(.content-body p) {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  :global(.content-body ul),
  :global(.content-body ol) {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  :global(.content-body li) {
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  :global(.content-body strong) {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  :global(.alert-box) {
    background: #fdfae9;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }

  .share-box {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #eee;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .back-link {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: bold;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: 0.2s;
  }
  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* Sidebar */
  .sticky-card {
    position: sticky;
    top: 120px;
    background: #fbfbfb;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
    border: 1px solid #eee;
  }

  .service-links ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }

  .service-links li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed #eee;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .service-links a {
    color: #666;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: 0.2s;
  }
  .service-links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 5px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .article-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
